quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,160,"Whoever comes [on the Day of Judgement] with a good deed will have ten times the like thereof [to his credit], and whoever comes with an evil deed will not be recompensed except the like thereof; and they will not be wronged.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., treated unjustly.
  6,161,"Say, "
  6,162,"Say, "
  7,70,"They said, ",footnotes:1:i.e., Allāh's punishment.
  7,71,"[Hūd] said, ",footnotes:1:The false objects of worship which you have called "gods."
  7,72,"So We saved him and those with him by mercy from Us. And We eliminated those who denied Our signs, and they were not [at all] believers."
  8,4,"Those are the believers, truly. For them are degrees [of high position] with their Lord and forgiveness and noble provision."
  8,5,"[It{1} is] just as when your Lord brought you out of your home [for the battle of Badr] in truth, while indeed, a party among the believers were unwilling,",footnotes:1:Referring to a dispute which occurred among the Muslims over distribution of war booty.
  8,6,"Arguing with you concerning the truth after it had become clear, as if they were being driven toward death while they were looking on."